5.2 Explain the client-server model with a neat diagram.
Ans--
The Client-Server Model is a distributed application structure that partitions tasks between providers of a resource (servers) and service requesters (clients).

->Client: The device/browser (like Chrome or Safari) that sends a request for data.
->Server: A powerful computer that stores files/databases and sends the requested data back.
------>Diagram<-------
[ Client ]  ---------- Request (HTTP) -------->  [ Server ]
 (Web Browser) <--------- Response (HTML/JS) ------ (Web Host)

